<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Apologies for posting so many requests for help lately, but a recent update of packages seems to have screwed up some features that were working quite well before.</p> <p>I now have an issue with alphapapa&#39;s <code>helm-org-rifle</code> package, which allows you to search through all currently open org files. Any time I call <code>helm-org-rifle</code>, I receive the error:</p> <pre><code>helm--run-init-hooks: ‘after-init-hook’ hook in source ‘xxx.org’ not specified as symbol function </code></pre> <p>where <code>xxx.org</code> is whatever the last viewed org file is. Below is the backtrace from <code>debug-on-error</code> after I call <code>helm-org-rifle</code>.</p> <pre><code>Debugger entered--Lisp error: (error &quot;‘after-init-hook’ hook in source ‘xxx.org’ not...&quot;) signal(error (&quot;‘after-init-hook’ hook in source ‘xxx.org’ not...&quot;)) error(&quot;`%s&#39; hook in source `%s&#39; not specified as symbol f...&quot; after-init-hook &quot;xxx.org&quot;) helm--run-init-hooks(after-init-hook (... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...)) helm-initial-setup(nil (... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...)) helm-initialize(nil nil nil (... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...)) helm-internal((... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...) nil nil nil nil nil nil nil nil) apply(helm-internal (... nil nil nil nil nil nil nil nil)) helm((... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...) nil nil nil nil nil nil nil nil) apply(helm (... nil nil nil nil nil nil nil nil)) helm(:sources (... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...)) helm-org-rifle() funcall-interactively(helm-org-rifle) call-interactively(helm-org-rifle nil nil) command-execute(helm-org-rifle) </code></pre> <p>Here are some additional points:</p> <ul> <li><p>The related <code>helm-org-rifle-occur</code> function seems to work totally fine, without any errors. I would just switch to this but I find it slightly less convenient.</p></li> <li><p>Closing all org file buffers in Emacs and calling <code>helm-org-rifle</code> doesn&#39;t give an error, but then the function is totally useless.</p></li> <li><p>I do have a general template for most org files, with a <code>#+SETUPFILE:</code> and <code>#+TITLE</code> etc. But I created a totally blank <code>.org</code> file, opened it in emacs, and did <code>helm-org-rifle</code> again - the same error came up again.</p></li> <li><p>The problem is most likely something to do with my config. But if I do <code>emacs -Q</code>, and load the bare minimum of stuff to get <code>helm-org-rifle</code> working (which as far as I can tell is doing <code>(require &#39;package)</code> and <code>(package-initialize)</code> and adding some load paths), I get the same error! </p></li> </ul> <p>Maybe the issue is that there&#39;s an update with <code>helm</code> itself that is causing this? I haven&#39;t found an issue on <code>github</code> about this yet.</p> <p>I&#39;m on Emacs <code>27.2</code>, with org version <code>9.4.4</code>, <code>helm</code> version <code>20220726.1622</code>, and <code>helm-org-rifle</code> version <code>20200512.1943</code>.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/nonreligious"> /u/nonreligious </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wc8zd2/helmorgrifle/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wc8zd2/helmorgrifle/">[comments]</a></span>